2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104190021.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20movie's%20basic%20story%20line%20is%20nothing%20to%20write%20home%20about%20-%20well-to-do%20millennials%20Alizeh%20and%20Ayan%20meet%20at%20a%20discotheque%20in%20London%2C%20she%20fresh%20from%20a%20breakup%20and%20he%2C%20well%2C%20in%20a%20not%20so%20serious%20relationship.%20After%20a%20hilarious%20and%20failed%20attempt%20at%20making%20out%2C%20the%20two%20become%20best%20friends%2C%20even%20taking%20a%20trip%20to%20Paris...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Ishita%20Sharma%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIndia%20Poised%20To%20Be%20Growth%20Engine%20Of%20World%26quot%3B%3A%20RBI%20Governor's%20Top%20Quotes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20poised%20to%20become%20new%20growth%20engine%20of%20world.%20Domestic%20economy%20exhibits%20resilience%20on%20back%20of%20strong%20demand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CRBI%20retains%20GDP%20growth%20forecast%20for%20current%20fiscal%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Freserve-bank-of-india-keeps-key-lending-rate-unchanged-at-6-5-for-fourth-consecutive-time-4454925%5C%22%3E6.5%20pc%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewith%20risks%20evenly%20balanced.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20forex%20reserves%20stood%20at%20%24586.9%20billion%20as%20on%20September%2029.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CInflation%20is%20likely%20to%20ease%20in%20September.%20Central%20bank%20forecasts%20retail%20inflation%20at%205.4%20pc%20for%202023-24.%20Retail%20inflation%20to%20moderate%20to%205.2%20per%20cent%20in%20next%20year%20from%20the%20current%20level%20of%206.8%20per%20cent.%20Our%20inflation%20target%20is%204%20per%20cent%2C%20not%202%20to%206%20per%20cent%3B%20we%20remain%20vigilant%20to%20evolving%20inflation%20target%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20banking%20system%20continues%20to%20be%20resilient%20on%20back%20of%20improved%20asset%20quality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BRBI%20has%20decided%20to%20double%20the%20gold%20loan%20under%20bullet%20payment%20scheme%20to%20Rs%204%20lakh%20for%20Urban%20Cooperative%20Banks%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696569840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-04%2F5fanfmco_rbi-governor-new-_625x300_06_April_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-poised-to-be-growth-engine-of-world-rbi-governors-top-quotes-4455109%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20decided%20to%20retain%20the%20policy%20rate%20for%20the%20fourth%20time%20in%20a%20row%2C%20RBI%20Governor%20Shaktikanta%20Das%20said%20today%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20closely%20monitoring%20inflation.%20The%20governor%20said%20the%20Monetary%20Policy%20Committee%20(MPC)%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-poised-to-be-growth-engine-of-world-rbi-governors-top-quotes-4455109%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-poised-to-be-growth-engine-of-world-rbi-governors-top-quotes-4455109%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-poised-to-be-growth-engine-of-world-rbi-governors-top-quotes-4455109%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Review%3A%20Mission%20Raniganj%20-%20Engineer%20Played%20By%20Akshay%20Deserved%20A%20Better%20Film%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20unprecedented%20rescue%20of%2065%20trapped%20miners%20by%20a%20real-life%20hero%2C%20a%20Coal%20India%20officer%20who%20put%20his%20life%20on%20the%20line%20in%20the%20process%2C%20is%20reenacted%20in%20%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20directed%20by%20Tinu%20Suresh%20Desai%20and%20written%20by%20Vipul%20K.%20Rawal.%20The%20film%20is%20marred%20by%20excesses%20of%20the%20kind%20that%20leave%20no%20room%20for%20addressing%20themes%20beyond%20the%20surface%20of%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20set%20in%20Mahabir%20Colliery%20in%20West%20Bengal's%20Raniganj%20area%2C%20does%20not%20dig%20deep%20enough%20as%20it%20mines%20the%20story%20of%20Jaswant%20Singh%20Gill%2C%20an%20intrepid%20engineer%20whose%20valour%20is%20part%20of%20Indian%20mining%20folklore.%20The%20man%20deserved%20a%20much%20better%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20reinforces%20the%20lingering%20belief%20that%20Hindi%20cinema%20should%20leave%20true%20stories%20alone%2C%20especially%20if%20Akshay%20Kumar%20is%20to%20be%20placed%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20action.%20%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%3C%2Fem%3E%20suffers%20the%20deleterious%20consequences%20of%20the%20spotlight%20being%20focused%20on%20the%20star%20rather%20than%20on%20the%20issues%20surrounding%20the%20mining%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECast%20your%20mind%20back%20to%20%3Cem%3EKala%20Patthar%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Yash%20Chopra's%201979%20film%2C%20inspired%20mainly%20by%20the%20Chasnala%20mining%20tragedy%20from%20four%20years%20earlier%20and%20partly%20by%20Joseph%20Conrad's%20Lord%20Jim%2C%20had%20a%20disgraced%20Merchant%20Navy%20captain%20who%20sought%20redemption%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20earth.%20The%20principal%20character%20and%20the%20story%20had%20layers%20that%20imparted%20power%20to%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20does%20have%20references%20to%20Chasnala%20in%20passing%2C%20has%20no%20depth%20of%20any%20sort.%20Barring%20the%20pretty%20obvious%20unwaveringly%20good%20guy%20versus%20a%20bunch%20of%20bad%20(and%20worse%2C%20lazy)%20guys%20and%20a%20mining%20disaster%20construct%2C%20the%20film%20has%20little%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGill%20is%20reduced%20to%20a%20single-note%20character%20and%20his%20incredible%20story%20is%20rendered%20merely%20as%20an%20ear-splitting%2C%20broad%20strokes%20spectacle.%20The%20lead%20actor's%20limited-bandwidth%20performance%20is%20of%20no%20help.%20As%20the%20makers%20of%20this%20film%20envision%20him%2C%20he%20is%20a%20larger-than-life%20figure%20who%20isn't%20assailed%20by%20any%20doubts%20or%20moments%20of%20weakness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUndeterred%20by%20the%20chaos%20around%20him%20and%20never%20dithering%2C%20he%20goes%20about%20the%20job%20of%20saving%20the%20workers%20gasping%20for%20breath%20in%20an%20inundated%20coal%20mining%20pit%20as%20if%20he%20were%20a%20man%20strolling%20in%20a%20park.%20The%20enormity%20of%20his%20achievement%20-%20he%20devises%20an%20untested%20rescue%20method%20-%20and%20the%20magnitude%20of%20his%20courage%20and%20commitment%20are%20undermined%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGill's%20pregnant%20wife%2C%20Nirdosh%20Kaur%20(Parineeti%20Chopra%2C%20seen%20in%20four%20and%20a%20half%20sequences)%2C%20is%20an%20epitome%20of%20fortitude%20and%20patience.%20When%20her%20husband%20advises%20her%20to%20exercise%20caution%2C%20she%20retorts%20that%20women%20back%20in%20her%20pind%20(village)%20work%20in%20the%20fields%20one%20day%20and%20go%20into%20labour%20the%20very%20next%20day%20without%20batting%20an%20eyelid.%20Contrast%20that%20with%20the%20locals%2C%20men%20and%20women%20alike%20-%20they%20are%20either%20despairing%20crybabies%20or%20habitual%20no-hopers%20who%20cannot%20do%20without%20a%20saviour%20from%20a%20land%20of%20warriors.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20trapped%20miners%20-%20among%20them%20are%20men%20played%20by%20Ravi%20Kishan%2C%20Sudhir%20Pandey%2C%20Jameel%20Khan%20and%20Omkar%20Das%20Manikpuri%20-%20bicker%20incessantly%20as%20their%20chances%20of%20getting%20out%20alive%20recede%2C%20oxygen%20levels%20fall%20%C2%A0and%20the%20water%20that%20has%20gushed%20into%20the%20pit%20gets%20closer%20to%20the%20elevated%20part%20of%20the%20channel%20that%20they%20have%20sought%20refuge%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FQFf91hnpClI%3Fsi%3DIia57hk6WhcU9QPo%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20desperate%20men%20are%20frequently%20at%20each%20other's%20throats%20and%2C%20as%20panic%20mounts%2C%20do%20everything%20in%20their%20power%20to%20jeopardise%20their%20own%20lives.%20Their%20distressed%20family%20members%2C%20mostly%20women%20and%20elderly%20men%2C%20rave%20and%20rant%20and%20howl%20and%20holler.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20having%20lost%20hope%20of%20seeing%20her%20son%20again%2C%20slaps%20Gill%20in%20the%20heat%20of%20the%20moment%20only%20to%20regret%20her%20action%20soon%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20takes%20it%20on%20the%20chin%20and%20continues%20to%20do%20what%20has%20got%20to%20be%20done%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20miners%20are%20rescued%20even%20as%20a%20bunch%20of%20recalcitrant%20Bengalis%20try%20to%20make%20things%20difficult%20for%20him.%20This%20bunch%20of%20men%20is%20led%20by%20mining%20engineer%20D.%20Sen%20(Dibyendu%20Bhattacharya)%2C%20a%20well-worn%20pop-culture%20stereotype%20of%20the%20slothful%20native%20of%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESen%2C%20stationed%20in%20Ranchi%2C%20is%20the%20villain%20of%20the%20story.%20He%20claims%20that%20he%20knows%20the%20area%20like%20the%20back%20of%20his%20hand%20and%20should%2C%20therefore%2C%20be%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20rescue%20operation.%20He%20wants%20to%20see%20Jaswant%20Singh's%20daring%20mission%20fail%20because%20he%20cannot%20stand%20the%20Mahabir%20Colliery%20chief%20R.J.%20Ujjwal%20(Kumud%20Mishra).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHis%20disruptive%20interventions%20border%20on%20the%20farcical%20as%20does%20his%20general%20demeanour.%20He%20is%20shown%20eating%2C%20drinking%20hot%20milk%2C%20putting%20his%20feet%20up%20without%20a%20care%20in%20the%20world%20and%20getting%20a%20lackey%20to%20massage%20him%20while%20Gill%20and%20his%20team%20do%20not%20so%20much%20as%20take%20a%20single%20breather.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Raniganj%20mine%20crisis%20occurred%20in%20November%201989%20in%20the%20coal%20belt%20of%20West%20Bengal%20on%20the%20border%20of%20what%20was%20Bihar%20back%20then.%20The%20Left%20Front%20was%20in%20its%20third%20term%20as%20the%20ruling%20formation%20in%20Calcutta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20film%20offers%20frequent%20flashes%20of%20red%20party%20flags%20being%20waved%20in%20the%20background%2C%20it%20isn't%20interested%20in%20exploring%20the%20impact%20of%20trade%20unionism%20on%20the%20mines%20or%20questions%20of%20safety%20measures%20and%20working%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20have%20required%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20research%20as%20well%20as%20knowledge%20and%20understanding%20of%20contemporary%20state-level%20politics%20and%20the%20workings%20of%20Coal%20India.%20All%20this%20is%20beyond%20the%20makers'%20ken.%20So%20they%20choose%20the%20easiest%20way%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20pits%20a%20fearless%20and%20fastidious%20North%20Indian%20knight%20in%20shining%20armour%20not%20just%20against%20a%20mining%20accident%20of%20daunting%20proportions%20but%20also%20against%20a%20bunch%20of%20not%20just%20unhelpful%20but%20also%20corrupt%2C%20cowardly%20and%20self-serving%20locals%2C%20which%20includes%20a%20smarmy%20politician%2C%20Gobardhan%20Roy%20(Rajesh%20Sharma).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bashing%20of%20Bengalis%20assumes%20a%20literal%20form%20late%20in%20the%20film%20when%20one%20of%20them%20is%20subjected%20to%20lathi%20blows%20by%20a%20man%20who%20holds%20him%20and%20his%20ilk%20responsible%20for%20giving%20Bengal%20a%20bad%20name.%20In%20a%20crunch%20situation%2C%20Sen%20exhorts%20his%20two%20assistants%2C%20a%20Sengupta%20and%20a%20Roy%2C%20to%20show%20the%20world%20what%20a%20Royal%20Bengal%20Tiger%20is%20made%20of.%20The%20pair%20develops%20cold%20feet.%20The%20'tigers'%20chicken%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%20%3C%2Fem%3Eopens%20with%20a%20sequence%20in%20which%20a%20workers'%20leader%2C%20a%20blustery%20Bengali%20of%20course%2C%20demands%20the%20reinstatement%20of%20a%20miner%20dismissed%20from%20service%20on%20the%20charge%20of%20being%20drunk%20on%20duty.%20In%20walks%20Gill%20and%20puts%20the%20man%20in%20his%20place.%20Suitably%20chastened%20by%20the%20Sardar's%20iron-fist-in-velvet-gloves%20toughness%2C%20he%20beats%20a%20hasty%20retreat.%20We%20immediately%20know%20what%20the%20protagonist%20is%20up%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20would%20be%20dismissed%20as%20plain%20silly%20had%20the%20film's%20superficial%20ways%20not%20undermined%20the%20innately%20dramatic%20tale%20so%20irretrievably.%20%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20sort%20of%20film%20that%20manages%20to%20reduce%20an%20actor%20of%20Kumud%20Mishra's%20range%20to%20a%20nonentity.%20He%20struggles%20to%20breathe%20life%20into%20a%20man%20who%20is%20grappling%20with%20blood%20pressure%20and%20sinking%20spirits%20and%20who%20is%2C%20therefore.%20compelled%20to%20let%20Gill%20hog%20the%20limelight.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20all%20that%20one%20can%20say%20about%20a%20film%20that%20makes%20a%20hash%20of%20a%20wonderful%20tale%20of%20grit%2C%20gumption%20and%20glory%20is%3A%20what%20a%20disaster!%20%3Cem%3EMission%20Raniganj%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20high-intensity%20drama%20undermined%20by%20low-calibre%20filmmaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696569660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fhmqmf7m_akshay-_625x300_06_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fmission-raniganj-review-the-intrepid-engineer-played-by-akshay-kumar-deserved-a-much-better-film-1-5-stars-4455099%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mission%20Raniganj%20Review%3A%20The%20film%20reinforces%20the%20lingering%20belief%20that%20Hindi%20cinema%20should%20leave%20true%20stories%20alone%2C%20especially%20if%20Akshay%20Kumar%20is%20to%20be%20placed%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20action.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fmission-raniganj-review-the-intrepid-engineer-played-by-akshay-kumar-deserved-a-much-better-film-1-5-stars-4455099%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Is%20Modern%20Indian%20Architecture%20So%20Banal%20and%20the%20Cities%20So%20Unlivable%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05151749%2F11797815225_491834355e_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20recent%20article%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20titled%20%E2%80%98Why%20Conserving%20Modern%20Architecture%20Has%20Become%20Nearly%20Impossible%E2%80%99%20raised%20several%20questions%20that%20have%20been%20worrying%20architects%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20series%20of%20demolitions%20and%20planned%20demolitions%20of%20post-independence%20buildings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20country%20is%20emerging%20from%20a%20long%20stretch%20of%20European%20colonisation%20and%20is%20finding%20its%20feet%20amongst%20the%20arts%20and%20architecture%20of%20the%20modern%20age.%20But%20European%20influence%20still%20plays%20a%20role%20in%20this%20quest%20for%20what%20is%20Indian%20and%20what%20is%20mere%20copy.%20It%20has%20been%20difficult%20for%20Indian%20architects%20to%20create%20a%20style%20that%20adequately%20presents%20a%20rising%20civilisation%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20its%20own%20denizens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20country%20that%20has%20produced%20so%20many%20beautiful%20buildings%20over%20the%20centuries%20is%20now%20having%20to%20formulate%20its%20identity%20and%20design%20of%20buildings.%20Take%20the%20Hall%20of%20Nations%2C%20designed%20by%20Raj%20Rewal%20and%20built%20in%20the%201970s%20to%20provide%20a%20space%20for%20international%20exhibitions%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Delhi.%20Before%20it%20was%20demolished%20by%20this%20government%2C%20it%20was%20arguably%20one%20of%20the%20finest%20works%20of%20architecture%20in%20the%20post-Independence%20era.%20It%20represented%20a%20new%20approach%20and%20borrowed%20nothing%20from%20Bauhaus%20ideologies%20or%20from%20Le%20Corbusier%E2%80%99s%20enormous%20influence.%20The%20architect%20found%20a%20way%20to%20build%20a%20unique%20structure%20that%20was%20modern%20and%20monumental.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F02%2FHall-of-Nations.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Hall%20of%20Nations.%20Credit%3A%20The%20Wire%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221267%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-112805%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22429%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Hall%20of%20Nations.%20Credit%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnfortunately%2C%20our%20administrators%20felt%20it%20occupied%20a%20very%20valuable%20amount%20of%20real%20estate%20and%20they%20had%20no%20understanding%20of%20its%20historic%20value%20and%20proceeded%20to%20tear%20it%20down.%20By%20this%20logic%2C%20one%20could%20argue%20that%20the%20Purana%20Qila%20(%E2%80%98Old%20Fort%E2%80%99)%20%E2%80%93%20built%20by%20Humayun%20in%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20which%20lies%20next%20to%20Pragati%20Maidan%20where%20the%20exhibition%20grounds%20are%20located%20and%20also%20occupies%20valuable%20land%20in%20the%20city%20centre%20%E2%80%93%20should%20be%20demolished%20too.%20Luckily%2C%20the%20fort%20is%20under%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20Preservation%20of%20Ancient%20Monuments%20Act%2C%201958.%20Indian%20architects%20are%20now%20suggesting%20that%20a%20new%20act%20be%20brought%20in%20to%20protect%20architectural%20buildings%20of%20significance%2C%20regardless%20of%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20British%20decided%20to%20shift%20their%20Capital%20to%20Delhi%20from%20Kolkata%2C%20they%20chose%20a%20large%20area%20adjacent%20to%20Shahjanabad%2C%20the%20capital%20created%20by%20the%20Mughal%20emperor%20Shah%20Jahan.%20They%20designed%20and%20built%20an%20imperial%20city%20that%20was%20to%20last%20a%20thousand%20years%20(something%20we%20have%20heard%20before%20and%20since).%20But%20after%20just%2025%20years%2C%20they%20had%20to%20abandon%20the%20capital.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20New%20Delhi%20was%20created%20as%20a%20set%20of%20imposing%20buildings%20that%20exhibited%20the%20might%20of%20the%20British%20Empire.%20The%20present%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan%20was%20originally%20the%20residence%20of%20the%20Viceroy%2C%20who%20was%20the%20representative%20of%20the%20King%20of%20England.%20The%20North%20and%20South%20Blocks%2C%20while%20architectural%20masterpieces%20of%20colonial%20design%2C%20were%20intended%20to%20rule%20India%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Jewel%20in%20their%20Crown%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20Union%20governments%20of%20independent%20India%20have%20been%20hypnotised%20by%20these%20imperial%20buildings.%20The%20president%20of%20India%20lives%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20Viceregal%20Lodge%20and%20the%20main%20ministries%20of%20home%2C%20defence%2C%20finance%20and%20external%20affairs%20are%20ensconced%20in%20the%20Secretariat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMinisters%20sit%20in%20their%20grand%20teak-panelled%20offices%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Indian%20civil%20services%20continue%20to%20enjoy%20their%20pre-Independence%20pomp%20and%20glory.%20The%20present%20regime%20has%20tried%20to%20bring%20about%20change%20and%20has%20built%20new%20buildings%20along%20the%20main%20vista%20that%20was%20once%20called%20Rajpath%2C%20later%20Janpath%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98people%E2%80%99s%20way%E2%80%99%20and%20now%20Kartavyapath.%20All%20of%20these%20are%20signifiers%20of%20an%20India%20that%20continues%20to%20be%20ruled%20rather%20than%20governed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05150421%2FRashtrapati_Bhavan_1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05150421%2FRashtrapati_Bhavan_1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05150421%2FRashtrapati_Bhavan_1-300x161.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05150421%2FRashtrapati_Bhavan_1-1024x549.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678438%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22643%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EForecourt%20of%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan.%20Photo%3A%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan%2C%20GODL-India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20prescient%20Gandhi%20saw%20the%20impact%20these%20imperial%20buildings%20would%20have%20on%20those%20in%20power%20and%2C%20after%20Independence%2C%20pleaded%20with%20the%20state%20to%20create%20another%20capital%20that%20would%20leave%20the%20British%20legacy%20behind.%20It%20would%20have%20been%20simple%20to%20acquire%20land%20at%20that%20time%20but%20instead%2C%20we%20now%20have%20the%20satellite%20towns%20of%20Noida%20and%20Gurugram%20which%20are%20really%20vast%20suburbs%20of%20concrete%2C%20steel%20and%20glass.%20A%20faceless%20set%20of%20buildings%20that%20appears%20in%20rings%20of%20roads%20around%20the%20capital%20of%20Delhi%20housing%20millions%20of%20residents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20course%2C%20it%20is%20not%20as%20if%20Indian%20governments%20were%20the%20only%20ones%20seduced%20by%20grand%20buildings%3A%20the%20new%20rulers%20of%20Russia%20used%20the%20Kremlin%20palaces%20(the%20old%20residences%20of%20the%20Czars)%20as%20their%20headquarters%20and%20the%20Chinese%20used%20the%20palaces%20of%20the%20Forbidden%20City%20(residences%20of%20Emperors%20for%20several%20centuries)%20as%20the%20staging%20post%20for%20their%20May%20Day%20parades.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArchitecture%20plays%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20manner%20cities%20are%20planned%20and%20the%20remains%20of%20a%20civilisation%20are%20largely%20seen%20through%20the%20buildings%20that%20are%20left%20behind.%20Architects%20are%20told%20not%20to%20hark%20back%20to%20history%20but%20how%20is%20it%20possible%20to%20ignore%20Nalanda%2C%20Sanchi%20and%20Ellora%20%E2%80%93%20all%20treasures%20of%20design%20created%20by%20previous%20civilisations%3F%20Today%20we%20are%20reduced%20to%20banal%20edifices%20of%20square%20and%20round%20skyscrapers%20that%20represent%20what%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20term%20prosperity%20and%20development.%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20creating%20a%20recognisably%20distinct%20Indian%20civilization%20is%20fast%20disappearing%20as%20the%20subcontinent%E2%80%99s%20buildings%20try%20to%20replicate%20the%20tiny%20principalities%20of%20Dubai%20and%20Singapore.%20However%2C%20these%20replicas%20do%20not%20match%20the%20quality%20or%20scale%20of%20the%20modern%20age%20%E2%80%98wonders%E2%80%99%20seen%20in%20the%20global%20cities.%20Will%20our%20present%20civilisation%20be%20seen%20a%20few%20centuries%20from%20now%20as%20piles%20of%20twisted%20metal%20and%20shards%20of%20glass%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENone%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20cities%20offers%20a%20solution%20for%20the%20modern%20city.%20They%20are%20all%20increasingly%20becoming%20unlivable%2C%20making%20the%20privileged%20few%20seek%20second%20homes%20in%20Goa%2C%20in%20hill%20stations%20or%20abroad.%20A%20chance%20to%20see%20real%20change%20was%20available%20when%20a%20capital%20was%20envisaged%20for%20the%20residual%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20state.%20It%20was%20to%20be%20called%20Amaravati%2C%20after%20the%20Buddhist%20capital%20that%20was%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20old%20kingdoms%20of%20this%20area.%20(Few%20know%20that%20people%20in%20the%20land%20that%20is%20now%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20followed%20the%20Buddhist%20faith%20for%20800%20years.)%20However%2C%20after%20several%20attempts%2C%20the%20present%20state%20government%20chose%20to%20make%20three%20capital%20regions%20and%20power%20was%20decentralised%20%E2%80%93%20a%20smart%20decision%20given%20the%20length%20of%20the%20state.%20But%20these%20different%20capitals%20just%20had%20more%20rings%20of%20suburbs%20where%20concrete%20and%20glass%20thrive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20this%20sounds%20very%20bleak%20and%20indeed%20it%20is.%20The%20future%20of%20Indian%20architecture%20and%20its%20habitat%20is%20represented%20by%20a%20few%20grand%20villas%20in%20Goa%20and%20some%20oversized%20air-conditioned%20flats%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Delhi.%20It%20is%20therefore%20important%20for%20architects%20to%20attempt%20to%20bring%20cityscapes%20together%20and%20create%20new%20designs%20that%20are%20community-driven.%20Colaba%2C%20a%20suburb%20of%20Mumbai%2C%20is%20a%20classic%20example%20of%20a%20settlement%20where%20the%20rich%20and%20poor%20mingle%20and%20live%20complete%20lives.%20It%20is%20a%20microcosm%20of%20the%20mighty%20%E2%80%98maximum%20city%E2%80%99%20and%20is%20a%20place%20where%20everything%20is%20available%20and%20some%20protection%20is%20offered%20to%20heritage%20buildings.%20Re-use%20of%20buildings%20is%20being%20done%20and%20an%20excellent%20example%20is%20the%20cafe%20built%20inside%20a%20former%20godown%20which%20was%20gutted%20and%20the%20exterior%20kept%20intact.%20Another%20well-known%20renovation%20is%20an%20ice%20factory%20in%20Ballard%20Estate%20that%20has%20been%20converted%20into%20a%20modern%20gallery%20and%20exhibition%20space%20for%20events.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmongst%20the%20other%20major%20cities%20of%20India%2C%20Mylapore%20within%20the%20city%20of%20Chennai%20is%20a%20good%20example%20that%20has%20coexisted%20since%20the%20inception%20of%20the%20city.%20Many%20British%20residents%20made%20this%20area%20into%20their%20homes%20and%20while%20it%20is%20in%20good%20condition%20can%20be%20well%20restored%20for%20the%20reuse%20of%20a%20cityscape.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20old%20city%20of%20Hyderabad%20with%20the%20Charminar%20as%20its%20focus%20is%20also%20an%20independent%20settlement%20within%20the%20megapolis%20of%20the%20modern%20capital%20and%20is%20quite%20independent%20of%20the%20chaos%20of%20modern%20Hyderabad.%20Due%20to%20its%20antiquity%2C%20the%20inhabitants%20live%20and%20work%20on%20an%20%E2%80%98island%E2%80%99%20with%20their%20own%20economy.%20Many%20other%20cities%20in%20India%20have%20these%20qualities%20%E2%80%93%20with%20Jodhpur%2C%20Lucknow%20and%20Kolkata%20among%20the%20largest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F03170625%2FCharminar.hydrabad.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22charminar%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F03170625%2FCharminar.hydrabad.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F03170625%2FCharminar.hydrabad-300x169.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-496339%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECharminar.%20Photo%3A%20Vandana%20And%20Vaibhav%2F%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2F%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20may%20not%20be%20perfectly%20pleasing%20for%20aspiring%20architects%20who%20want%20to%20design%20magnificent%20edifices%20but%20they%20may%20have%20to%20start%20making%20buildings%20that%20are%20more%20on%20a%20human%20scale.%20If%20new%20cities%20are%20to%20be%20made%20(and%20several%20are%20needed%20to%20cope%20with%20increasing%20numbers)%2C%20then%20the%20planning%20will%20have%20to%20be%20on%20a%20gigantic%20scale.%20The%20Kingdom%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20has%20embarked%20on%20building%20a%20170-km-long%20linear%20city%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FThe_Line%2C_Saudi_Arabia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98The%20Line%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20city%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20look%20to%20the%20past%2C%20attempts%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20future%2C%20and%20has%20big%20names%20and%20big%20money%20undergirding%20it.%20There%20are%20several%20aspects%20to%20the%20project%20that%20raise%20questions%20but%20the%20attempt%20to%20think%20anew%20is%20to%20be%20recognised.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20wealth%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20its%20population%20and%20its%20needs%20%E2%80%93%20will%20rise%20dramatically%20in%20the%20next%20decades%20and%20hence%20will%20have%20to%20consider%20something%20as%20spectacular%20and%20monumental%20as%20The%20Line%20City%20envisaged%20in%20the%20desert.%20The%20country%20has%20to%20decide%20whether%20it%20is%20going%20to%20pursue%20the%20limits%20of%20wealth%20which%20will%20sooner%20or%20later%20implode%20as%20the%20planet%20does%20not%20have%20the%20resources%20for%20this%20growth%20or%20follow%20a%20path%20that%20will%20allow%20the%20planet%20to%20survive%20the%20upheavals%20and%20lifestyles%20of%20the%20modern%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERamu%20Katakan%20is%20an%20architect.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696569345000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05151749%2F11797815225_491834355e_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fmodern-indian-architecture-banal-cities-unlivable%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20present%20period%20will%20be%20seen%20centuries%20later%20as%20piles%20of%20steel%20and%20shards%20of%20glass.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fmodern-indian-architecture-banal-cities-unlivable%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20endorses%20Jim%20Jordan%20for%20House%20speaker%2C%20testing%20the%20strength%20of%20his%20power%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Republican%20Rep.%20Jim%20Jordan%20of%20Ohio%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20House%20Judiciary%20Committee.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d66b885e5d5a00195c6c9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERepublican%20Rep.%20Jim%20Jordan%20of%20Ohio%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20House%20Judiciary%20Committee.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ETrump%20has%20endorsed%20Rep.%20Jim%20Jordan%20of%20Ohio%20to%20be%20the%20next%20Speaker%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20former%20president%20offered%20his%20backing%20in%20an%20early%20morning%20post%20on%20Truth%20Social.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EJordan%20and%20House%20Majority%20Leader%20Steve%20Scalise%20are%20now%20the%20two%20biggest%20names%20running%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20early%20on%20Friday%20morning%2C%20endorsed%20Republican%20Rep.%20Jim%20Jordan%20of%20Ohio%20to%20be%20the%20next%20Speaker%20of%20the%20House%2C%20testing%20his%20ability%20to%20bring%20calm%20to%20Congress%20after%20a%20week%20of%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongressman%20Jim%20Jordan%20has%20been%20a%20STAR%20long%20before%20making%20his%20very%20successful%20journey%20to%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20representing%20Ohio's%204th%20Congressional%20District%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20wrote%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%2C%20Truth%2C%20not%20long%20after%20midnight%20on%20the%20East%20Coast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20endorsement%20will%20likely%20upend%20the%20campaign%20to%20replace%20former%20House%20Speaker%20Kevin%20McCarthy%2C%20who%20was%20unceremoniously%20ousted%20earlier%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20race%20is%20largely%20between%20Jordan%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20House%20Judiciary%20Committee%2C%20and%20House%20Majority%20Leader%20Steve%20Scalise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president's%20decision%20to%20offer%20his%20backing%20is%20not%20without%20risk.%20Eighteen%20House%20Republicans%20represent%20districts%20that%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20won.%20They%20will%20now%20be%20forced%20to%20either%20defy%20Trump's%20will%20or%20potentially%20risk%20being%20tagged%20as%20too%20close%20to%20a%20figure%20who%20remains%20toxic%20for%20many%20of%20their%20voters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20Friday%20announcement%20also%20means%20that%20Trump%20is%20almost%20certainly%20done%20with%20floating%20the%20possibility%20of%20his%20own%20speakership.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-expect-trump-to-become-house-speaker-anytime-soon-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDespite%20skepticism%20from%20across%20Washington%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20former%20president%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-accept-house-speaker-role-kevin-mccarthy-republicans-gaetz-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinued%20to%20stoke%20speculation%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20he%20could%20seize%20upon%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20House%20does%20not%20technically%20have%20to%20be%20a%20member%20of%20Congress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20endorsement%2C%20the%20former%20president%20devoted%20significant%20praise%20to%20Jordan's%20prolific%20NCAA%20wrestling%20career%2C%20writing%3A%20%26quot%3BSo%20much%20is%20learned%20from%20sports%2C%20and%20Jim%20was%20a%20master!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cleveland.com%2Fopen%2F2023%2F10%2Fjim-jordan-has-denied-he-knew-about-sex-abuse-on-ohio-state-wrestling-team-heres-who-says-he-knew-and-who-says-he-didnt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJordan%20has%20faced%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20he%20failed%20to%20stop%20sexual%20abuse%20within%20the%20Ohio%20State%20wrestling%20program%2C%20accusations%20he%20has%20repeatedly%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Jordan%2C%20Trump%20is%20backing%20a%20staunch%20conservative%20fighter.%20The%20Ohio%20Republican%20has%20been%20a%20central%20figure%20in%20investigations%20of%20President%20Biden%20and%20his%20son%20Hunter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20this%2C%20Jordan%20served%20on%20the%20Select%20Committee%20that%20investigated%20the%202012%20attack%20on%20the%20US%20diplomatic%20compound%20in%20Benghazi.%20Jordan%20has%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-gop-speaker-race-issues-scalise-jordan-ukraine-gaetz-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpressed%20skepticism%20over%20further%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20position%20more%20in%20line%20with%20Trump's%20than%20Scalise%2C%20who%20voted%20for%20%24300%20million%20in%20aid%20just%20last%20week.%20While%20McCarthy%20tried%2C%20ultimately%20unsuccessfully%2C%20to%20placate%20the%20far-right%2C%20Jordan%20has%20been%20a%20core%20right-wing%20figure%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouse%20Republicans%20have%20set%20next%20Wednesday%20as%20the%20deadline%20to%20name%20a%20new%20speaker.%20They%20will%20first%20vote%20via%20secret%20ballot%20behind%20closed%20doors%20for%20the%20GOP%20conference%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20the%20party%20would%20only%20vote%2