%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20such%20an%20attack%20was%20detected%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bsuch%20a%20number%20of%20our%20missiles%20-%20hundreds%2C%20hundreds%20-%20would%20appear%20in%20the%20air%20that%20not%20a%20single%20enemy%20would%20have%20a%20chance%20of%20survival%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20not%20conducted%20a%20test%20involving%20a%20nuclear%20explosion%20since%201990%2C%20the%20year%20before%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20but%20Putin%20declined%20to%20rule%20out%20the%20possibility%20it%20could%20resume%20such%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20the%20United%20States%20had%20not%20ratified%20the%20treaty%20that%20bans%20nuclear%20tests%2C%20whereas%20Russia%20had%20both%20signed%20and%20ratified%20it.%20It%20would%20be%20theoretically%20possible%20for%20the%20Duma%2C%20Russia's%20parliament%2C%20to%20revoke%20its%20ratification%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMilitary%20analysts%20say%20a%20resumption%20of%20nuclear%20testing%20by%20Russia%2C%20the%20United%20States%20or%20both%20would%20be%20profoundly%20destabilising%20at%20a%20time%20when%20tensions%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20are%20greater%20than%20at%20any%20time%20in%20the%20past%2060%20years.%20In%20February%2C%20Putin%20suspended%20Russia's%20participation%20in%20the%20New%20START%20treaty%20that%20limits%20the%20number%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20each%20side%20can%20deploy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20no%20need%2C%20Putin%20said%2C%20for%20Russia%20to%20rewrite%20its%20doctrine%20on%20the%20actual%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20which%20says%20it%20may%20fire%20them%20either%20in%20response%20to%20a%20nuclear%20strike%20against%20it%20or%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20question%20from%20Russian%20analyst%20Sergei%20Karaganov%2C%20who%20has%20advocated%20lowering%20the%20threshold%20for%20nuclear%20use%2C%20Putin%20said%3A%