%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20victory%2C%20Muizzu%20had%20reiterated%20that%20his%20administration%20would%20commence%20work%20on%20removing%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20from%20the%20first%20day%20of%20his%20job.%20His%20presidential%20term%20will%20be%20inaugurated%20on%20November%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20weekly%20media%20briefing%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%2C%20answering%20questions%20about%20the%20new%20Maldives%20President-elect%E2%80%99s%20statements%20on%20Indian%20troops%2C%20said%20that%20there%20was%20need%20to%20work%20closely%20on%20regional%20security%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20I%20would%20say%E2%80%A6%20the%20focus%20of%20our%20partnership%20with%20the%20Maldives%20has%20always%20been%20on%20capacity%20building%20and%20working%20together%20to%20address%20our%20shared%20challenges%20and%20priorities%2C%20including%20security%20challenges%20and%20priorities.%20As%20neighbours%2C%20we%20need%20to%20collaborate%20closely%20to%20address%20these%20challenges%20confronting%20our%20region%2C%20such%20as%20transnational%20crimes%20and%20Humanitarian%20and%20Disaster%20Relief%20situations.%20We%20look%20forward%20to%20engaging%20with%20the%20new%20administration%20in%20the%20Maldives%20with%20all%20these%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBagchi%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20had%20been%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfirst%20leader%E2%80%9D%20to%20congratulate%20Muizzu%20on%20his%20victory%20on%20Sunday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%20me%20take%20the%20opportunity%20to%20congratulate%20the%20Maldivian%20people%20for%20once%20again%20demonstrating%20their%20faith%20in%20democratic%20governance%20and%20constitutional%20processes%20that%20reflect%20their%20firm%20commitment%20to%20the%20values%20of%20democracy%20and%20rule%20of%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20high%20commissioner%20Munu%20Mahawar%20called%20on%20the%20president-elect%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20also%20handed%20over%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20Indian%20leader.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20had%20a%20good%20discussion%20on%20various%20aspects%20of%20our%20bilateral%20partnership%2C%20including%20development%20cooperation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20president-elect%E2%80%99s%20office%20had%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F85103%5C%22%3Ereadout%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20discussions%20in%20Mal%C3%A9%20that%20Muizzu%20had%20said%20that%20he%20hoped%20to%20%E2%80%9Crestore%20relations%20with%20India%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20respect%20for%20sovereignty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMuizzu%2C%20as%20per%20his%20office%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Maldivian%20people%20had%20voted%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20sovereignty%2C%20and%20expressed%20confidence%20India%20will%20respect%20the%20decision%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20repayment%20of%20loans%20taken%20by%20the%20Solih%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAssuring%20that%20India%20will%20fully%20respect%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20independence%20and%20sovereignty%2C%20Mahawar%20responded%20that%20New%20Delhi%20was%20ready%20to%20negotiate%20debt%20repayment%2C%20according%20to%20the%20president-elect%E2%80%99s%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.mv%2Fnews%2F29480%5C%22%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EMihaaru%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Muizzu%20said%20that%20the%20most%20pressing%20issue%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20resolved%20once%20he%20assumes%20office%20is%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20issues%20listed%20were%20the%20large%20debt%20owed%20to%20India%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20Indian%20troops%20in%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20foreign%20troops%2C%20we%20do%20not%20have%20any%20problems.%20If%20we%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20speak%20for%20ourselves%20in%20the%20affairs%20of%20our%20country%20and%20what%20our%20country%20has%20to%20say%20on%20other%20platforms%20in%20the%20world%2C%20then%20we%20would%20not%20have%20issues%20with%20any%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Muizzu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Solih%20administration%20had%20repeatedly%20denied%20that%20there%20was%20any%20Indian%20military%20activity%20in%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20large%20projects%20funded%20by%20India%2C%20he%20said%20that%20there%20were%20no%20issues%20as%20long%20as%20there%20were%20no%20military%20personnel%20posted%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20example%2C%20when%20the%20Hanimaadhoo%20Airport%20is%20built%2C%20there%20will%20be%20engineers%20there.%20But%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20be%20%5BIndian%5D%20soldiers.%20Being%20a%20soldier%20is%20the%20problem.%20We%20have%20to%20ask%20them%20to%20sort%20it%20out.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20sorted%20out.%20Civilians%20have%20to%20be%20there%20to%20work.%20Even%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20wear%20the%20uniform%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20there%20are%20military%20personnel%2C%E2%80%9D%20Muizzu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldivian%20outlet%20also%20asked%20Muizzu%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-biggest-stakeholder-indian-ocean-region-advisor-muizzu%5C%22%3Eabout%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20quoted%20his%20foreign%20affairs%20adviser%20Mohammed%20Hussain%20Shareef%20%E2%80%98Mundhu%E2%80%99%20as%20saying%20that%20the%20first%20foreign%20visit%20would%20be%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20his%20remarks%2C%20Muizzue%20told%20%3Cem%3EMihaaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENews%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20he%20believed%20that%20the%20tradition%20of%20new%20Maldivian%20presidents%20making%20their%20first%20visit%20to%20India%20should%20continue.%20He%20said%20that%2C%20given%20the%20current%20situation%2C%20it%20would%20be%20ideal%20for%20him%20to%20make%20his%20first%20trip%20to%20India%2C%20but%20that%20no%20decision%20has%20still%20been%20made%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696526022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F30231028%2FThe-Wire-27.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmaldives-president-elect-calls-for-sovereignty-india-stresses-cooperation-on-security-challenges%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20his%20victory%2C%20Muizzu%20had%20reiterated%20that%20his%20administration%20would%20commence%20work%20on%20removing%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20from%20the%20first%20day%20of%20his%20job.%20His%20presidential%20term%20will%20be%20inaugurated%20on%20November%2017.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmaldives-president-elect-calls-for-sovereignty-india-stresses-cooperation-on-security-challenges%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SAT%20Quashes%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20Insider%20Trading%20Order%20Against%20NDTV%20Co-Founders%20Prannoy%20Roy%20and%20Radhika%20Roy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F02162103%2FUntitled-design-58-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Securities%20Appellate%20Tribunal%20(SAT)%20has%20quashed%20an%20insider%20trading%20order%20by%20capital%20markets%20regulator%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20against%20Prannoy%20Roy%20and%20Radhika%20Roy%2C%20the%20co-founders%20of%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20order%2C%20issued%20by%20SEBI%20in%20November%202020%2C%20accused%20them%20of%20insider%20trading%20and%20barred%20them%20from%20accessing%20the%20capital%20markets%20for%20two%20years.%20It%20had%20directed%20them%20to%20disgorge%20the%20amount%20wrongfully%20gained%20%E2%80%93%20over%20Rs%2016.97%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%206%25%20interest%20per%20annum.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsat-overturns-sebi-order-against-ndtv-founders-prannoy-roy-radhika-roy-123100500836_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20SAT%20overturned%20the%20order%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20information%20scrutinised%20by%20SEBI%20was%20not%20price-sensitive%2C%20and%20the%20Roys%20were%20not%20insiders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20find%20that%20Prannoy%20Roy%20and%20Radhika%20Roy%20received%20pre-trade%20clearance%20from%20NDTV%E2%80%99s%20compliance%20officer%2C%20a%20fact%20acknowledged%20in%20the%20show%20cause%20notice.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20trades%20executed%20by%20these%20two%20individuals%20were%20in%20line%20with%20NDTV%E2%80%99s%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20and%20the%20PIT%20Regulations%2C%E2%80%9D%20SAT%20observed%2C%20per%20the%20business%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20pertained%20to%20trades%20conducted%20between%20September%202007%20and%20April%202008%2C%20involving%20allegations%20of%20an%20illicit%20gain%20of%20nearly%20Rs%2017%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20SAT%20order%20vindicates%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20more%20than%20two%20years%20ago%20when%20the%20top%20court%20stayed%20the%20SEBI%20order%20and%20ruled%20that%20Radhika%20and%20Prannoy%20Roy%20do%20not%20have%20to%20pay%20any%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESEBI%20had%20on%20December%2024%2C%202020%20imposed%20Rs%2027%20crore%20penalty%20on%20the%20three%20NDTV%20promoters%20%E2%80%93%20Prannoy%20Roy%2C%20Radhika%20Roy%20and%20RRPR%20Holding%20Limited%20%E2%80%93%20for%20failing%20to%20disclose%20price-sensitive%20information%20to%20shareholders%20of%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202021%2C%20SAT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fmarkets%2Fstocks%2Fnews%2Fsat-directs-ndtvs-prannoy-roy-radhika-roy-to-deposit-50-of-disgorged-amount%2Farticleshow%2F80212233.cms%5C%22%3Edirected%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20NDTV%20promoters%20to%20deposit%2050%25%20of%20the%20disgorged%20amount%20before%20SEBI%20within%20four%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20February%20of%20that%20year%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fmarkets%2Fstocks%2Fnews%2Fhear-appeals-of-ndtv-promoters-without-insisting-on-deposit-of-sebis-fine-sc-tells-sat%2Farticleshow%2F80923750.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Edirected%3C%2Fa%3E%20SAT%20not%20to%20insist%20on%20deposit%20of%20fines%20as%20a%20pre-condition%20for%20hearing%20their%20appeals%20against%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2027%2C%202021%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-ndtv-prannoy-roy-radhika-roy-27cr-penalty-sebi-171783%5C%22%3Estayed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20recovery%20of%20penalty%20on%20the%20NDTV%20promoters.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696524569000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F02162103%2FUntitled-design-58-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsat-quashes-sebis-insider-trading-order-against-ndtv-co-founders-prannoy-roy-and-radhika-roy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SAT%20said%20that%20the%20information%20scrutinised%20by%20SEBI%20was%20not%20price-sensitive%2C%20and%20the%20Roys%20were%20not%20insiders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsat-quashes-sebis-insider-trading-order-against-ndtv-co-founders-prannoy-roy-and-radhika-roy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ahead%20of%20Telangana%20Elections%2C%20EC%20Removes%2022%20Lakh%20Voter%20Names%20From%20Electoral%20Rolls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%2