20early%20in%20%3Cem%3EKhufiya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20when%20KM%20while%20describing%20a%20mole%20on%20someone%E2%80%99s%20neck%2C%20takes%20a%20neat%20segue%20to%20talk%20about%20another%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%98mole%E2%80%99%20working%20in%20her%20agency.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20the%20last%20time%20we%20hear%20something%20like%20that%20in%20the%20160-minute%20film.%20Known%20otherwise%20for%20his%20irreverence%20and%20wit%2C%20%3Cem%3EKhufiya%3C%2Fem%3E%20might%20be%20Bhardwaj%E2%80%99s%20most%20painfully%20literal%20and%20pedantic%20film%20%E2%80%93%20where%20a%20traitor%20is%20codenamed%20%E2%80%98Brutus%E2%80%99%2C%20an%20asset%20is%20called%20%E2%80%98Octopus%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20where%20an%20asset%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98encoded%E2%80%99%20message%20to%20her%20handler%20is%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20weather%20is%20clear%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20attribute%20of%20most%20worlds%20in%20Bhardwaj%E2%80%99s%20films%20is%20how%20they%20appear%20to%20already%20be%20in%20orbit%2C%20before%20the%20movie%20catches%20up.%20In%20%3Cem%3EKhufiya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20almost%20appears%20like%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20characters%20are%20discovering%20the%20world.%20So%20even%20though%20the%20likes%20of%20KM%20and%20her%20group%20are%20shown%20to%20be%20pros%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20make%20rookie%20mistakes.%20For%20example%20not%20being%20prepared%20for%20the%20most%20predictable%20outcome%20when%20they%E2%80%99re%20bugging%20someone%E2%80%99s%20house%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20residents%20will%20turn%20up%20before%20they%E2%80%99re%20expected%20to.%20If%20the%20intent%20was%20to%20show%20how%20%E2%80%9Creal-life%E2%80%9D%20spies%20can%20be%20clumsy%2C%20it%20never%20really%20comes%20across.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FByojhBwG_-E%3Fsi%3DiejCgYFQlk7Zg55c%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBhardwaj%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKhufiya%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20straightforward%20film%20about%20spycraft%2C%20which%20feels%20more%20dense%20than%20it%20should%20because%20of%20its%20convoluted%20telling.%20Based%20on%20Amar%20Bhushan%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EEscape%20to%20Nowhere%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20film%20is%20set%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Kargil%20war%2C%20where%20India%E2%80%99s%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20ISI%20are%20trying%20to%20influence%20elections%20in%20Bangladesh.%20The%20main%20%E2%80%9Cvillain%E2%80%9D%20here%20is%20a%20corrupt%20Defence%20minister%20Mirza%20(Shataf%20Figar)%20in%20Bangladesh%20%E2%80%93%20a%20puppet%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20ISI.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20Tabu%E2%80%99s%20team%20and%20her%20asset%20%E2%80%98Octopus%E2%80%99%20(Azmeri%20Haque)%20come%20in%20%E2%80%93%20to%20track%20Mirza%E2%80%99s%20whereabouts.%20However%2C%20Octopus%20is%20discovered%2C%20because%20of%20a%20mole%20in%20R%26amp%3BAW.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnand%20Mohan%20(Ali%20Fazal)%20is%20a%20mid-level%20intelligence%20operative%20at%20R%26amp%3BAW%2C%20suspected%20of%20being%20the%20traitor.%20Living%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20Charu%20(Wamiqa%20Gabbi)%2C%20elderly%20mother%20(Navnindra%20Behl)%20and%20a%20five-year-old%20son%20in%20a%20posh%20South%20Delhi%20residence%2C%20Fazal%20is%20a%20fluid%20presence%20as%20someone%20who%20seemingly%20develops%20a%20taste%20for%20the%20good%20life%2C%20but%20is%20also%20believable%20as%20a%20loving%20husband%20and%20dutiful%20son.%20Gabbi%20is%20a%20revelation%20alongside%20Fazal%2C%20who%20next%20to%20a%20mostly%20sedate%20Tabu%2C%20always%20seems%20inches%20away%20from%20eagerly%20bursting%20into%20more%20than%20one%20expression%20in%20any%20given%20scene.%20KM%20and%20her%20crew%20observe%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20hoping%20to%20catch%20him%20red-handed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20major%20shortcoming%20for%20%3Cem%3EKhufiya%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20even%20when%20the%20plot-twists%20catch%20us%20off%20guard%2C%20they%20never%20lend%20insight%20into%20the%20characters%20who%20they%20are.%20Who%20is%20Krishna%20beyond%20her%20patriotism%2C%20longing%20for%20a%20lover%20from%20the%20past%2C%20and%20overseeing%20the%20remains%20of%20a%20broken%20marriage%20next%20to%20a%20man%20gracefully%20telling%20her%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20her%20fault%3F%20Who%20is%20Anand%20beyond%20someone%20who%20got%20seduced%20by%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20good%20life%3F%20How%20does%20betrayal%20change%20someone%20as%20happy-go-lucky%20as%20Charu%20into%20what%20she%20becomes%20in%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20second%20half%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20almost%20sense%20the%20reluctance%20in%20Bhardwaj%2C%20to%20go%20ahead%20and%20model%20a%20character%20on%20Sadhguru%20%E2%80%93%20a%20%E2%80%98rockstar%E2%80%99%20guru%20called%20Yaara%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20(played%20by%20real-life%20musician%2C%20Rahul%20Ram)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20provides%20a%20tether%20to%20help%20Charu%20track%20down%20Anand.%20The%20parody%20feels%20too%20cautious%20and%20on-the-nose%2C%20hardly%20something%20one%20usually%20associates%20with%20Bhardwaj.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20almost%20160-minute%20runtime%2C%20it%20simultaneously%20feels%20like%20too%20much%20happens%20in%20%3Cem%3EKhufiya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20not%20enough%20happens.%20There%20are%20weird%20contrivances%20joining%20plot-points%20together%20that%20will%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20(blind)%20faith%20in%20Bhardwaj%20as%20a%20storyteller.%20But%20there%20are%20also%20scenes%20where%20Bhardwaj%20and%20his%20co-writer%20Rohan%20Narula%20dwell%20for%20inordinately%20long%20periods%2C%20robbing%20the%20film%20off%20its%20briskness.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20film%20that%20gives%20the%20illusion%20of%20being%20busy%20on%20a%20narrative%20level%2C%20especially%20the%20way%20Bhardwaj%20employs%20flashbacks%20%E2%80%93%20but%20when%20serially%20arranged%20to