r%20Literature%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05170623%2Fjon.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Swedish%20Academy%20on%20Thursday%20awarded%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20Nobel%20Prize%20for%20Literature.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20year%E2%80%99s%20winner%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fnorway%2Ft-18943636%5C%22%3ENorwegian%3C%2Fa%3E%20author%20Jon%20Fosse.%20The%20academy%20hailed%20his%20%E2%80%9Cinnovative%20plays%C2%A0and%20prose%20which%20give%20voice%20to%20the%20unsayable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20master%20of%20contemporary%20theatre%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201959%20in%20the%20Norwegian%20coastal%20town%20of%20Haugesund%2C%20Jon%20Fosse%20is%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20contemporary%20European%20writers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20been%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Beckett%20of%20the%2021st%20century%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20French%20daily%20%3Cem%3ELe%20Monde%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20as%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20most%20provocative%20pens%20in%20contemporary%20theatre%2C%E2%80%9D%20by%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EGlobe%20%26amp%3B%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFosse%20published%20his%20first%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3ERed%2C%20Black%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%201983.%20He%20has%20since%20published%20numerous%20novels%2C%20stories%2C%20books%20of%20poetry%2C%20essay%20collections%20and%20even%20children%E2%80%99s%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20first%20play%2C%20whose%20English%20title%20is%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20We%E2%80%99ll%20Never%20Be%20Parted%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20published%20in%201994%2C%20the%20prolific%20author%20went%20on%20to%20write%20some%2040%20theatrical%20pieces.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHis%20international%20breakthrough%20as%20a%20playwright%20came%20with%20the%201999%20staging%20of%20%3Cem%3ESomeone%20Is%20Going%20to%20Come%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20late%20French%20theatre%20director%20Claude%20Regy.%20The%20play%20centres%20on%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20who%20move%20to%20a%20run-down%20house%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20nowhere%20to%20be%20alone%2C%20but%20quickly%20become%20paranoid%20that%20%E2%80%9Csomeone%20is%20going%20to%20come%2C%E2%80%9D%20sparking%20hidden%20jealousies%20within%20the%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Booker%20Prize%20website%2C%20his%20plays%20have%20since%20been%20staged%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20times%20around%20the%20world%20in%2050%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFellow%20Norwegian%20author%20Karl%20Ove%20Knausgaard%2C%20who%20used%20to%20be%20his%20student%2C%20details%20how%20influential%20Fosse%E2%80%99s%20work%20was%20for%20him%20in%20%3Cem%3EMy%20Struggle%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20made%20Chevalier%20of%20the%20Ordre%20national%20du%20Merite%20of%20France%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20one-sentence%20magnum%20opus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFosse%E2%80%99s%20magnum%20opus%20is%20his%20%3Cem%3ESeptology%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20published%20in%20three%20volumes%20from%202019-2021%20under%20the%20titles%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Other%20Name%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EI%20Is%20Another%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EA%20New%20Name%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThrough%20a%20single-sentence%20monologue%20of%20an%20elderly%20artist%20talking%20to%20himself%2C%20the%201%2C250-page%C2%A0prose%20work%20offers%20a%20bleak%20but%20ecstatic%20reflection%20on%20art%20and%20God.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFosse%20has%20told%20%3Cem%3ENew%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%20that%20the%20ageing%20artist%E2%80%99s%20reckoning%20with%20religion%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20autobiographical%20at%20all%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20the%20Norwegian%20author%20had%20his%20own%20religious%20awakening%20a%20decade%20ago.%20Until%202012%2C%20he%20described%20himself%20as%20an%20atheist%2C%20but%20then%20joined%20the%20Catholic%20Church%20and%20underwent%20at%20the%20same%20period%20rehab%20to%20overcome%20his%20long-term%20alcohol%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20critically%20acclaimed%20work%20was%20shortlisted%20for%20several%20prizes%2C%20including%20the%20National%20Book%20Award%20and%20the%20International%20Booker%20Prize.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20spends%20his%20time%20between%20his%20homes%20in%20Austria%2C%20in%20Oslo%20and%20in%20the%20western%20part%20of%20Norway.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBetween%20his%20own%20writing%20projects%2C%20Fosse%20has%20also%20translated%20other%20authors%E2%80%99%20works%2C%20including%20Kafka%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Trial%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20he%20describes%20as%20one%20of%20his%20favourite%20novels.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Literature%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Nobel%20Prize%C2%A0is%20worth%2011%20million%20Swedish%20crowns%20(%24990%2C000%2C%20%E2%82%AC948%2C000).%C2%A0Last%20year%E2%80%99s%20winner%20was%20French%20author%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwhat-are-the-antisemitism-claims-linked-to-nobel-prize-winner-annie-ernaux%2Fa-63403179%5C%22%3EAnnie%20Ernaux%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whom%20the%20Swedish%20Academy%20praised%20for%20%E2%80%9Ccourage%20and%20critical%20acuity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fjon-fosse-wins-nobel-prize-for-literature%2Fa-67004466%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%3A%3Athewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26di%3D%26an%3D%26ac%3D%26x1%3D1%26x2%3D2%26x5%3Dthewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26x6%3D1%26x8%3Den-VAS-Volltexte-JavaScript-thewire.in-dwde%26x10%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pub