ing%20majority%20of%20454-2%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%20tabled%20in%201996%2C%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20pending%20legislations%20in%20Parliament.%20It%20took%20eight%20different%20governments%2C%2027%20years%2C%20and%20a%20fight%20by%20women%20across%20the%20country%20to%20make%20this%20Bill%20a%20reality.%20Presently%2C%20there%20are%20102%20women%20parliamentarians%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20766%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20only%2013%20percent.%20This%20Bill%20is%20much%20needed%2C%20as%20India%20ranks%20141%20in%20women%20representation%20in%20parliament%2C%20as%20per%20an%20Inter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(IPU)%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20historic%20bill%20is%20here%20today%20thanks%20to%20the%20efforts%20of%20many%20women%20politicians%20and%20activists%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F328785%2Fimportant-letters-from-nehru-gandhi-sigmund-freud-that-shaped-india-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPramila%20Dandavate%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20MP%20from%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20had%20first%20introduced%20this%20Bill%20as%20a%20private%20member%E2%80%99s%20Bill%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20in%20the%20seventh%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20VP%20Singh%20government%20in%201989%2C%20she%20was%20the%20one%20who%20first%20demanded%2033%20percent%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Parliament%20and%20Vidhan%20Sabha.%20This%20trailblazer%20started%20writing%20charters%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20women%20behind%20the%20victory%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20582px)%20100vw%2C%20582px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill4-1695994589.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22582%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pramila%20Dandavat